Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Pop a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Pick the @tarragon{1} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). When the oven is hot, pop the @serrano ham{2} onto a #baking tray{} and cook on the top shelf of your oven until crisp and golden, ~{5-7%mins}. Crumble the serrano when it's cooled set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of oil in a large #frying pan{} on a medium-high heat. When hot, add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%mins}. Add the garlic and cook for a further ~{1%minute}. Add the @water{100%ml}, chopped tarragon and @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Stir together, bring to a boil and cook for ~{1-2%mins}.

Meanwhile, pop the @wholegrain mustard{8.5%g}, @honey{15%g} and @olive oil{1/2%tbsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch} into a #bowl{}, mix.

> TIP: If the dressing is too thick, loosen with a splash of water.

Roughly chop the @walnuts{20%g} and pop them into the bowl too. Set aside.

Once the sauce has come to a boil, turn the heat down to a simmer. Add the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @king prawns{225%g}, stir to mix well and simmer until the prawns have cooked through, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when they are pink all the way through.

Whilst the prawns cook, add the @fresh tagliatelle{200%g} to the pan of boiling water and cook until tender, ~{3-4%mins}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it from sticking together.

Pop the @wild rocket{20%g} into the bowl with the walnuts and mustard dressing, mix well to dress. Stir the pasta through the creamy prawn sauce.

> TIP: Add a splash more water if the sauce is dry.

Share between your plates. Top with serrano crumb and serve the rocket salad on the side. Enjoy!